relations.head: Interferon alpha
relations.label: phosphorylate
relations.text: Treatment of cells with IFN-alpha caused these three proteins to be phosphorylated on tyrosine and to translocate to the cell nucleus where they stimulate transcription through binding to IFN-alpha-stimulated response elements in DNA.

relations.head: Interferon gamma
relations.label: phosphorylate
relations.text: IFN-gamma, which activates transcription through a different receptor and different DNA binding sites, also caused tyrosine phosphorylation of one of these proteins.

relations.head: ISGF3 alpha proteins
relations.label: bind
relations.text: Treatment of cells with IFN-alpha caused these three proteins to be phosphorylated on tyrosine and to translocate to the cell nucleus where they stimulate transcription through binding to IFN-alpha-stimulated response elements in DNA.
